The way people live and think affects how they make business deals. When we talk about a group's way of life, we must be careful not to make simple statements like "all people from one country act the same way." Each group is different, and people within groups are different too.

When we meet people from other places, we often compare them to what we know. To work well with people from other places, we need to learn about their history and ways of thinking. We should not try to change how they live or think. Instead, we should accept their ways, especially when we want to make deals with them. When we go to their country, showing respect for their traditions helps create better business relationships.

Groups can be different even within the same country. Companies often have their own ways of doing things. Some want workers to stay late at work, while others let workers leave earlier. You can see how companies are different by looking at what clothes workers wear, how they talk to each other, and who they choose to hire. Some companies want workers to help poor people, while others only give money to special groups. Even in America, companies in different places can be very different from each other.

What people think is important tells us why they act in certain ways. If people think it is important not to lose respect, they will not do things that shame their company or their boss. If people think it is important to get the best price, they may not agree to a deal quickly. It helps to know these things before making business deals. It is also good to learn about the person you are dealing with, not just their group's ways.

The Bible says, "The person without wisdom says there is no God." This idea appears in two important religious writings by Anselm and Thomas Aquinas. Both men tried to prove that God exists. To compare their ideas fairly, we must accept that they are talking about the God described in the Bible. While both writers make good points, neither gives a complete reason to believe in God.

Let us first look at what Anselm says. He believes that we can find proof of God by looking inside ourselves. His main idea is that because we can understand the idea of God in our minds, God must exist. He thinks we do not need to look for proof outside ourselves. We only need to think about what we already know in our hearts. This way of believing without seeing clear proof is called faith.

Thomas Aquinas has a different view. He says we can prove God exists by using careful thinking and by looking at the world around us. This approach would help spread Christianity because people would not need faith to believe. They would only need to follow clear thinking. Aquinas gives five different reasons to prove God exists. He looks at how things change, how everything has a cause, why things exist, why some things are better than others, and how nature works together. His ideas are like solving a puzzle. If you put most of a puzzle together and one piece is missing, you can know what the missing piece looks like without seeing it.

Writers often try to make readers feel certain ways about important things in their stories. F. Scott Fitzgerald does this well in his book The Great Gatsby. He puts words together in special ways to create feelings. He also uses colors to mean special things in the story.

In The Great Gatsby, Fitzgerald gives special meaning to colors like white, gray, red, and pink. He uses these colors carefully to make readers remember certain feelings about important things in the story.

White and gray in the story often show sameness. White usually means clean and rich, while gray shows age and tiredness. From the start, many people wear white in the story. Daisy and Jordan are "in white." Nick wears "white clothes" to Gatsby's party. Tom has on a "white shirt" when he sees Myrtle. Catherine's face is very white with powder.

Fitzgerald uses white and gray to show common, everyday things too. Nick goes to work through "white streets" in New York. The names of people at parties become "gray names" in Nick's notes. Many buildings look the same, like "white cake." Simple people and places are often white or gray in the story. The poor areas have "gray cars" and "gray land." A "gray old man" sells dogs.

After giving these colors their special meaning, Fitzgerald uses them to tell us more about people, especially Daisy. When we see Daisy "dressed in white" in her "white car," we start to see her differently. She becomes less special and more like everything else - just something Gatsby wants. Her fur collar is "gray," and she wears white again before an important meeting with Tom and Gatsby. These colors help show that Daisy may not be as special as Gatsby thinks.

San Diego County grows many foods because of its warm, sunny weather. Farmers grow tomatoes, oranges, green leaves for food, and other vegetables. They also grow fruits like peaches and lemons. They make honey and grow hot peppers too.

Many people in San Diego want to buy food grown without chemicals. They often join waiting lists to get this food from local farms. These farms also let people visit to see how food grows. People can walk on the land and watch birds there. Farm owners can get money from the government to help keep the land good for animals while still growing food.

Growing food without chemicals helps more kinds of plants and animals live on the land. But this way of farming costs more money. Workers must pull out bad plants by hand and find other ways to stop bugs from eating the food. Small farms also lose more food than big farms. To help wild animals, farmers must do extra work like planting special plants and moving their animals to different fields at different times. Because of these costs, farmers often need help with money.

The land in this story sits next to the town of Potrero in San Diego County. It covers 160 acres next to a big forest. The land has many kinds of plants and trees. It is home to special animals that need help to live, like rare rats, frogs, and birds.

Native American people lived on this land for many years. Later, in the late 1800s, people came to raise cows and cut wood there. Someone got this land from the government long ago and probably used it for cows or wood since then.

I found this land for sale and looked up ways the government could help a small farmer. I also found another farm nearby that grows food without chemicals to use as an example.

Brothers share a special connection that cannot be broken. This connection brings many feelings like love, pride, anger, and sometimes even meanness. Brothers know each other better than anyone else can. When they look at each other, they see themselves. This truth becomes most clear when things are very hard. The results of these feelings can bring much pain. Brothers must learn to deal with what happens because of their feelings. When they look at each other, they see who they really are, not who others think they are. Their true nature shows in what they do and what happens after.

In the story "The Scarlet Ibis," two brothers show us these ideas. They travel through beautiful green lands on a trip that cannot succeed. One brother feels very proud while the other feels very sad. At the end, only one brother lives. We see this through the older brother's thoughts and actions with Doodle, his younger brother. The older brother tells us the story and shows us his complex feelings about his world, which shape what he does.

The older brother's actions come from his pride. From the first time he takes Doodle outside until their last walk together, he feels unhappy with his brother. He wanted a brother who could do things with him, like hold his breath, run, jump, and climb trees. He wanted someone to race with and sit with high in the pine trees. But Doodle could not do these things. He was born with a weak heart, and doctors thought he would die. Even if he lived, he could never run or play hard. This made the older brother very sad and angry. He even thought about hurting baby Doodle with a pillow. But when Doodle smiled at him, the older brother's anger went away. This small act gave him hope. It shows that deep down, he truly loved his brother.

The human brain is an amazing system that processes information in complex ways. As humans created new things over time, they found different ways to explain how the brain works. First, they said it was like a flat piece of wax. Later, they said it was like paper, then a book, and now, people often say it is like a computer. However, these simple comparisons can sometimes lead to wrong ideas about the brain.

The brain first gets information from our senses, like touch, heat, sound, and light. This information changes into signals that the brain can understand. The brain then works with these signals in two ways. First, it looks at simple things like color and shape. Then, it uses what it knows to better understand what it sees. For example, when you see a black box on white paper, your brain first sees the colors and edges. Then, it helps you know that it is a box, not a hole in the paper.

The brain also decides what information is important. For instance, when you look at grass, you do not notice every small piece. But if someone says your name in a loud room, you might hear it clearly.

The brain must store information to use it. There are three main types of memory: quick memory (for things you just saw), working memory (for things you are thinking about now), and long-term memory (for things you remember from before). The brain changes information so it can be stored. For words, it can remember how they look, sound, or what they mean. Working memory lasts about twenty seconds. Long-term memory stays in the brain through special proteins.

Scientists have different ideas about how the brain organizes what we know. One idea says that the brain connects related things. For example, in your mind, the word "chair" connects to "table," which connects to "wood," and so on.

In 2007, the United States faced a very serious money problem. Many people lost their jobs. House prices fell sharply. Many big American companies failed. These problems continue today, so we must ask: why did this happen, and how can we prevent it?

The crisis started because banks gave home loans to people who could not pay them back. The government pushed banks to do this. Two big government-supported companies, Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac, helped make these bad loans into complex financial products. When people could not pay their loans, banks lost money. This hurt the whole economy.

The problems began in 1999 when Bill Clinton was president. He wanted to win more support from voters. His government made it easier for banks to give loans. This led to bigger problems later. A New York Times writer, Steven Holmes, warned about this in 1999. He wrote that Fannie Mae was being pushed to give more loans to people with low and middle incomes. He said this could cause serious problems if the economy got worse.

Several things made the problem bigger. Banks created new types of home loans that were hard to understand. They also created new ways to sell these loans to other companies. This meant that when house prices fell, it hurt many parts of the economy, not just housing.

When house prices finally dropped, many banks lost a lot of money. The five biggest U.S. investment banks had $4.1 trillion in housing debt in 2007. This was almost one-third of all the money made in America that year. Two big banks had to be sold for very low prices. One bank closed completely. Two others had to change how they did business. Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac lost so much money that the government had to take control of them in 2008.

Let's talk about telling stories. Writers often want to explain too much at once. This can make readers stop reading or feel bored.

It is better to show what happens than to just tell about it. Sometimes writers want to give all the background information first. They think this will help readers understand the story better. But this is usually not a good idea.

When you tell a story, you need to let things happen naturally. For example, think about telling a love story. You could simply say: "They met. They got married. He died." But this tells us nothing about who these people are or why we should care about them.

Instead, you should show how they fell in love. Let readers hear them talk to each other. Show what makes each person special. When readers care about the characters, they will feel sad when bad things happen to them.

Sometimes writers want to tell everything about a new character right away. They might want to say where the person worked before, what they do now, if they were married, and what they like to do. But it is better to let readers learn these things slowly, as the story moves forward.

Remember: good writing is like serving a full meal, not just giving basic facts. Take time to develop your story and your characters. Your readers will thank you for it.

I watched two news programs from Columbus, Ohio. The first one was on NBC 4 on the morning of August 13, 2011. The main story was about a man in Ashley, Ohio who had hurt his wife with a knife. The man's name was Shad Hostettler. His picture showed a very angry face. The story was short because it was still new. They only said he had hurt his wife many times and the police had caught him. I think they used the right amount of time for this story.

The second story was about a young man, Travis Buyers, who was 18 years old. Someone shot him in the Sharon Woods area, and he was very badly hurt. The police had not caught anyone yet. Special police teams were looking into what happened. The story seemed very short. I think this might be because the hurt man was black. I have seen for many years that when bad things happen to people who are not white, the news talks about it less. When something bad happens to white people, the news talks about it much more.

They then talked about a hole made by a gun in a medical flying machine. They said where they thought it happened. The shot came from a small gun. People who help catch bad people are offering money if someone can help find who did it.

The weather news said rain would come Saturday afternoon. They said it would not be too hot that weekend. They did not talk long about this because they wanted people to watch more later.

They also told about someone taking money from a store on Clime Road. They said a black man took the money. They talked a lot about how he looked and spent too much time talking about his skin color.

The last story was about a man named Rene Rodriguez who sold bad things in Texas. He tried to send these bad things to Ohio. They said he would go to jail for 300 months instead of saying 25 years. They also said he was Hispanic, which did not matter to the story.

Let me explain what an ETF is and how it works. An ETF (exchange traded fund) is a special kind of investment that works like both a group of stocks and a single stock. You can buy and sell it easily, just like a single company's stock.

When you buy an ETF, you are really buying small parts of many different companies at once. This helps reduce your risk because your money is spread across many businesses. ETFs usually cost less money to own than other similar investments.

There are some things to think about before buying ETFs. You must pay a small fee each time you buy or sell them. However, there are many different kinds of ETFs to choose from, which is good for investors.

In this study, we looked at an ETF called IHF to see if it was better to own the ETF or to buy the ten biggest companies in it separately. These ten companies make up about 64% of the entire ETF.

When we looked at the numbers, we found something interesting. If you owned just these ten companies in the same amounts as the ETF holds them, you could make about 16% more money than owning the ETF itself. The investment would also be less risky.

But we needed to make sure these differences were real and not just by chance. So we looked at how much these investments typically move up and down in price to see if the difference was important.

Looking at Figure 17, we saw a big drop in travel records during the third month. This was disappointing, and we were not sure why it happened. When winter comes to our school in the northeast United States, fewer people ride bikes or walk to work. This may explain part of the drop. December is also when the school term ends. Everyone is busy finishing work and giving grades. Many people may have forgotten to write down how they traveled. December is also a holiday month when students and teachers do not come to school for many days. School starts again in late January, which may explain why few people wrote records that month. But this does not explain why February had so few records. We think any project like this starts with much interest that then goes down. To fight this drop, we made a special week in March called Carpool Challenge Week. This helped increase the number of records that month. So, one of our problems was keeping people interested when they naturally lose interest, and when school breaks happen.

Another problem is that people like driving their own cars. They like being free to go where they want, when they want. This is part of our way of life. So, we needed to give people reasons to try other ways to travel. We gave many prizes like food store cards, coffee shop cards, and book store cards. We wonder if bigger prizes would have helped more people join - like giving away a good bike or a special car that uses less gas. This might have stopped the drop in interest. Our prizes stayed the same during the project. If we had made the prizes better over time, that might have helped. The gift cards worked well at first, but if we had said we would give away bikes in December and a special car in January, we think more people would have stayed interested.

I studied fifteen early films made by Thomas Edison between 1895 and 1901. These were special films that used clever ways to make things appear to happen that were not really possible. I wanted to understand how most of these films were made and what made some of them different from others.

Most of these special films were made in a way that was like watching a play on stage. The camera stayed in one place and showed everything from the front, like sitting in a theater. The camera did not move, and it showed the whole scene from far away or middle distance. Each film was usually just one single view.

These films were always made inside a building on a stage. The camera never moved to follow the people or things in the film. This way of making films came from theater shows and magic acts. Because of this, people in the films usually moved only from left to right across the stage. They did not walk toward or away from the camera. For example, in a film called "Uncle Josh in a Spooky Hotel" (1900), the actors come in from the right side and move back and forth across the stage. When they leave the picture, the camera stays still.

The way these films were made meant that everything was shown from far away, like watching a stage play. The camera never showed close pictures of faces or things. This was like being in a theater, where you see everything happening on the whole stage at once. The actors stayed in the middle of the stage and did not come close to the camera.

Most of these early special films were very short, usually less than one minute long. They showed simple tricks like making things appear, disappear, or change into something else. They did not tell long stories. Even though these films looked like one continuous view, they were actually made by joining different pieces of film together very carefully. For example, in "The Execution of Mary, Queen of Scots" (1895), if you look very carefully, you can see where they cut the film to make it look like her head was cut off.

The Gothic Novel is both old and new at the same time. Some people have said these stories are too simple, while others praise them for creating feelings of fear and wonder. The first Gothic Novel, "The Castle of Otranto" by Horace Walpole, mixed old story ideas with new ways of writing to create something different. 

Walpole used parts from old plays and new ways of writing about real life to tell what he called "A Gothic Story." The Gothic style borrowed many things from the Middle Ages, like the way buildings looked and how people lived then. When the book came out, the word "gothic" was used to talk about many different things from the past, and some people thought it was old-fashioned. But by mixing old Gothic ideas with the new way of writing novels, which let readers better understand what characters were thinking and feeling, these stories stayed popular for a long time.

One of the main ideas in Gothic novels is the idea of being noble and brave, which comes from the Middle Ages. This idea was very important to Gothic writers because they thought their own time did not have enough brave and honest people. Writers like Walpole used these old ideas to try to make their present time better. When Walpole wrote his book, his country was having political problems, and he was worried about the future. He may have thought that people in his time had lost the good qualities that people had in the past. We can see this in his book through characters like Frederic, who shows many noble qualities from the past.

Supply chain management is about moving goods from start to finish. It begins when a customer orders something and ends when they receive it. This process includes getting raw materials, making products, and sending them to customers.

Keith Oliver, who helped businesses work better, first used the term "supply chain management" in 1982. He explained how to plan and control the movement of goods to make customers happy quickly and well.

There are six main parts of a supply chain. These are: making things, getting supplies, keeping products ready, choosing where to put things, moving goods, and sharing information. Business leaders use these six parts to serve customers well.

Making products is the first and most important part. Leaders must know what customers want by looking at what people buy. This helps them decide what to make and how much to make. They also need to pick the best places to make things, thinking about how many they can make and how good they will be.

After choosing where to make products, leaders must plan when workers will work and how to keep machines running well. Every small thing matters in making products. If the plan is not good, it can waste time and money. For example, stores like Wal-Mart and Target have clear plans for everything, from how workers should dress to how trucks should bring goods to stores. Good plans help everyone work better together.

The second main part is getting supplies. Leaders must decide what each place can do best and when to ask other companies for help. Sometimes, different places make different parts of one product. Leaders might ask other companies to help make things to save money and work faster while still making good products.

Books from the time when Queen Victoria ruled England often describe small details and focus on rich people's lives. However, two famous books from this time, "Oliver Twist" and "Wuthering Heights," are different. These stories use mystery and strange events to help readers better understand why characters act and feel the way they do.

In "Oliver Twist," we often see strange dreams or dream-like moments. These help us understand what hurts Oliver inside and what he knows about the bad things happening to him. For example, when Oliver is shot, he later remembers it like a dream. In this memory, he thinks he hears two bad men, Sikes and Crackit, talking. He sees bright lights and hears loud noises. He feels pain but cannot do anything about it. Someone pulls him away, but he does not know who.

This dream-like memory shows us that Oliver has no control over what happens to him. He cannot help himself, even when his life is in danger. It seems that Fagin, a bad man who forces children to steal, has made Oliver feel helpless. Oliver does not even try to save himself anymore.

Time moves strangely in these moments. Day turns quickly to night, and the night feels both very long and very short. The silence is hard to bear, but the hours pass quickly.

Two years ago, I helped young students after school with their studies. While I could help with many subjects, I was best at teaching reading and writing. A teacher asked me to help a young boy named Adrian. He was about nine years old and had trouble reading.

I noticed something strange about how Adrian read. He knew some letters very well, but others confused him. Adrian came from a Latino family, but he spoke English perfectly. We kept working together until I met his mother one day. She came to the school while I was watching a few students. His mother only spoke Spanish. I knew a little Spanish, so we were able to talk. Then I understood the problem: Adrian could read, but he did not know the English letters well.

I share this story to show how language problems affect our schools, especially in California. Sometimes these problems are hard to see. Even when children speak English well, reading can be very hard for them. We all know this problem exists, but what can we do? For Adrian, the answer was simple: he needed help learning English letters and their sounds. But for children who do not speak much English, the answer is not so simple. We need many different ways to help.

Some schools teach in two languages. Some put students directly into English classes. Some use special teachers. All these ways can help, but no single way is enough. We need to use all of them together.

Teaching in two languages helps all students, not just those who speak Spanish first. Studies show that children in two-language programs do better in school than other students. Some people worry this wastes money and only helps a few students. This is not true. If we use these programs in all classes, every student would learn better. We do not need every teacher to speak two languages. Instead, we can have special helpers who speak both languages work with students.

From when we are young, many of us learn about something greater than ourselves. Some learn at church, others at different places of worship, and some look inside themselves for answers. Many accept the religious beliefs their parents teach them. Others completely reject these ideas, believing only in what they can see and know. People may follow one set of beliefs, then change to different ones later. Whatever way we choose, we try to understand life's big questions through our own views about faith. We look for something to guide us through dark times.

"A red bird," my father told me when I asked about his favorite bird. We sat on our front porch, hearing rain hit the metal roof while we smoked. Water poured from the roof edge, falling on the plants below. He looked into the rain, partly searching and partly thinking of old times. He had become much thinner, and his clothes hung loose on his body. His hair was less full than before. He kept looking at the rain, not meeting my eyes. I felt alone and scared. I could not talk to my father about how I would miss him because talking would make it too real. I hugged him, then moved my chair closer to his. Together, we watched the rain fall in the growing darkness of that summer evening.

My father died in December that year, just after my birthday. The medical treatments did not stop his pain, but kept him alive longer than doctors expected. I could not understand why he had to suffer more. I questioned why this would happen. At night, alone, I stopped praying. I thought if there was a God, He no longer heard me.

I did not want to watch my father die, so I stayed away. I could not watch the person who gave me life lose his own. I wanted to remember how he lived, not how he died. I knew my father better than anyone, and I knew he would not want his only child to watch him die. I stayed in bed for three days, waiting to hear news.

No one called to tell me when he died.

John Taylor was an early supporter of the Republican way of thinking. He worked mainly as a farmer, and this work, along with his short time in government, made him known for speaking strongly about personal freedom and government matters. His love of farming shaped almost all of his ideas about how government should work. He tried to protect and support farming, which he thought was the best kind of work, and this affected his views on power, law, and courts.

Taylor thought the United States had a special chance to make a perfect system. This was because the new country did not have old rules that would get in the way of making a government run by the people. He strongly believed that people have natural rights, and that these rights work together. If one right is taken away, all other rights become weaker. He said the government should not be able to touch these rights. Some people talked about life without rules, where strong and clever but bad people would win. Taylor said this must not happen in a proper society.

To make this good society, Taylor said we need a government that understands both the good and bad in people. He had strong beliefs about right and wrong. He said that since people run government, government shows both good and bad human qualities. He said good rules protect what people own, help farming grow, and stop big business from having too much power. He thought a government with good rules would work well even if the leaders were greedy. Taylor believed people always act for their own good, but this only becomes bad when people stop working for everyone's good and start taking from others. Good government must keep people's bad side in check, but people must watch the government carefully.

Taylor, like other strong Republicans of his time, wanted to follow the Constitution exactly as it was written. He wanted a small federal government that could only do what the Constitution clearly said it could do. He knew a big federal government would cost too much money and might become too controlling. But he also thought following just the words was dangerous. He said we must think about what the writers meant. He believed the Declaration of Independence was more important than the Constitution because it better showed that the United States was made up of separate states working together, not one big nation.

I looked down at the toilet, not thinking much about what I saw. My mind was calm as I studied the situation. Thoughts came and went quickly. My brain worked so well that it felt like I wasn't really thinking at all.

Once, an artist told me to buy a book called "The New Drawing on the Right Side of the Brain." Since I was six, I wanted to learn to draw. The book teaches everything about drawing, from how to hold a pencil to how our brain works with art. One lesson tells us to put a frame around what we want to draw. This makes a complex scene, like a bowl of fruit in a kitchen, become simple.

At that moment, looking at the toilet, I couldn't think about art frames. I just stood there, surprised. Famous artists like Picasso used blue colors, Monet liked green, and old Italian painters used many colors. If I were an artist, this would be my brown period.

My fingers touched the toilet handle, and my hand moved through the air. The water moved smoothly and clearly. Small pieces broke away and disappeared. Moving more quickly the second time, I pushed the handle again. The brown mess stayed at the bottom of the toilet, not moving.

I stood there in my work clothes, holding a mop, with my green tie feeling tight around my neck. I looked at what someone had left for the cleaning workers at Rite Aid. After trying to flush a few more times, I reached for toilet paper. I wrapped my hand with lots of paper until it looked like a thick glove. Then, I bent down and slowly put my hand into the toilet, like reaching into an oven for food.

Young people are dying while driving cars. Several things make driving very dangerous for the youngest drivers in America. Studies show that young minds are not fully ready to deal with the dangers of driving. Also, new drivers do not have enough practice. This lack of experience leads to more deadly crashes, cars turning over, driving too fast, and going off the road.

Young drivers have more problems when they drive with friends their age, which they often do. A study in Southern California showed that more crashes happen when young passengers are in the car.

Some states try to make young drivers safer by giving them special licenses. These licenses say when they can drive and do not let them carry other young people in their cars.

But these special licenses are only a short-term answer. The truth is that the youngest drivers, as a group, are not ready to handle the serious job of driving safely. One expert who studies human behavior thinks even age 18 is too young to drive. His studies show that people under age 20 often do dangerous things just for fun. It makes sense to wait until people are older to let them drive.

If we keep giving driver's licenses to young people, more will die on the roads. In the coming years, many more young people will want to drive, which could make the problem worse.

The answer could be simple. Schools could still teach driving, but no one under 18 would be allowed to drive a car. New drivers would still need to practice with teachers and adults for many hours before getting a full license. Because this is a problem across America, one law for the whole country would help protect young people everywhere.

This idea is not new, but it could save many lives.

This paper looks at a brain problem that affects how people process sounds. The condition is called Central Auditory Processing Disorder, or CAPD.

First, I will explain what CAPD is. People with CAPD can hear sounds normally. However, their brains cannot understand these sounds properly. For example, they may have trouble understanding words when there is other noise in the room.

Second, I will describe how doctors find out if someone has CAPD. There are signs that teachers and parents can watch for. These signs help doctors know when to test for the problem.

Last, I will share ways teachers can help students with CAPD learn better in regular classrooms.

CAPD was first noticed by doctors in the 1950s. They saw it while working with children who had trouble communicating. Since then, doctors have created many tests to check for CAPD.

People with CAPD may have several problems:
- They may not know where sounds come from
- They may have trouble telling different sounds apart
- They may not understand changes in voice tone
- They may find it hard to remember sounds in order
- They may have trouble picking out important sounds from background noise

To check if someone has CAPD, doctors watch how a person responds to different sounds. They may ask the person to:
- Answer questions about their hearing
- Listen to words or numbers and repeat them
- Pick out specific sounds from other noises

There is no single test that can show if someone has CAPD. Doctors often use many different tests to understand the problem. Scientists are still trying to learn what causes CAPD.

I want to work in social services to help children who have been hurt by their families. I also want to help families who are having problems. I believe I can bring important things to this work: helping others, showing respect, doing what is right, and always learning to do my job better. These values are not just important for the job - they are important to who I am.

I always knew I wanted to help people, but I was not sure how. In school, I saw many young people run away from their problems or deal with them in bad ways. This made me want to study how people think and act, so I got a degree in this field from Piedmont College in 2009. After school, I took some time to think about what to do next.

One summer day, I met a young boy at my friend's house. He was there because his parents were hurting him. The next day, he called the police about his parents. I went to help and told the police about my education. They asked me to talk to the parents. The parents tried to say their son was causing trouble and making things up. This made me sure I wanted to work helping children with family problems.

I also believe everyone should be treated fairly. Our society says each person is special, but often pushes people to be the same as others. I do not like this. In school, I showed this by looking different from others and standing up for people who were treated badly because they were different. I joined groups that helped people who were treated unfairly. I will keep working to make sure everyone is treated fairly.

This paper looks at how sleep problems can be understood in two ways: through body science and through social factors. The body science way looks at genes we get from our parents and health issues. The social way looks at how our environment, culture, and living conditions affect us.

Sleep problems can be put into different groups. Some start on their own, while others happen because of mental health issues or other health problems. The main sleep problem we will look at is when people cannot sleep well, which doctors call insomnia.

When people cannot sleep well for a month or more, doctors call this insomnia. Some people have the opposite problem - they sleep too much. Others might fall asleep suddenly during the day. There are also people who have trouble breathing while sleeping, or their body clock does not work right.

Scientists have found that special cells in the brain help control when we sleep and when we are awake. They did tests with mice to learn about these brain cells. They found that certain parts of these cells, called receptors, are very important for sleep. When these receptors work right, they help us sleep. When they do not work right, people may have trouble sleeping.

This information helps us understand why some people have trouble sleeping - it may run in families through their genes. If someone has sleep problems because of their genes, it can make school, work, and daily life harder.

I have been studying at University Park for more than two years now. Getting around on this large school ground is hard for many students, including me. When I first came here, I lived in East Halls, which is very far from the center of the school. Walking from my room in Stuart Hall to my classes in Willard building could take 25 minutes, especially when the weather was bad. 

An older student told me that not long ago, East Halls stood alone, far from other buildings. Now that empty land has new sports fields and big buildings. As our school grows bigger, it gets harder to move from place to place. The best answer to this problem is the bicycle. But just having bikes is not enough. Students need to use them, and the school needs to make it easier for bike riders.

A friend who started riding his bike again after many years told me he was sorry he ever stopped. He said bikes are the best way to get around. Riding a bike is good for your health and uses very little energy. A simple breakfast can give you power to ride many miles.

I now live away from school, but it is as far as some student rooms on campus. Getting a bike was the best thing I did this year. I have class in Thomas building, which would take 25 minutes to reach by walking. On my bike, I can get there in 5 minutes if I ride fast. The only problem is that Pollock Road, the fastest way there, can be hard to travel on.

Walking is fine, but I do not have enough time. Without my bike, I would have to walk everywhere. Walking to Thomas building every day would take 40 more minutes of my time. That means more than two hours every week just for one class. When you think about going to other classes and meetings, it takes too much time that I cannot waste.

In his book "Brave New World," writer Aldous Huxley warns us about problems with new machines and money-based systems. He creates a future world where things have gone wrong. In this world, people think the group is more important than any single person. They are taught from birth to only care about being happy right now.

The people in this world are like pieces in a game, controlled by powerful leaders. When we look at the book through the ideas of Karl Marx, we can see Huxley was worried about how society was changing. Marx's ideas about everyone being made the same and people being treated like things help us understand the book better.

The book makes fun of our money-based system. The common people do not know how they are being used by the rich and powerful. They only think about getting things for themselves. In the book, different groups of people - called Delta, Gamma, and others - are taught while they sleep to always want to buy and use more things. The leaders use this to control them.

The lower groups do not know they are being controlled. They believe in what they are told without thinking. Even the higher groups, called Alphas and Betas, mostly accept things as they are. Only a few people, like a character named Bernard, question the system.

In this future world, real friendships between different kinds of people do not exist. The characters seem simple, without much depth. This might show how Huxley thought machines and money were making people less human. There is no love in this world. Men only talk about how women look, and women talk openly about their physical relationships without feeling shame.

Each group accepts its place in society without complaint. This shows how the money system affects people. They obey completely because they are taught to think they are better than others as long as they keep buying things and following rules.

Four years ago, I studied Islam at my local college. In class, we often talked about whether Islam was a religion that promoted peace or conflict. This question seems even more important today. Since the events of September 11, 2001, I have seen how news organizations changed their view of Islam. At first, they were very negative. Now, they show much more acceptance of Islam in America. In 2001, it would have been hard to imagine having a presidential candidate like Barack Obama, who has family members who were Muslim.

The life story of Muhammad interests me because what I read seems different from what I learned before. I had thought Muhammad made people join his religion by force when he took control of their lands. However, the book shows him as a good man who was not understood by others. It says people came to him on their own to learn his teachings.

I noticed that some stories about Muhammad are very similar to stories about Jesus. For example, there is a story where Muhammad took a small amount of food and made it enough to feed forty men. This reminds me of Jesus' miracles. I think the writers wanted to make Muhammad seem like a humble teacher who did not need to prove himself. This bothers me because it seems to copy the special things Jesus did.

The book has many stories about people becoming Muslim. However, these stories often come from people who heard them from other people, who heard them from others. This makes me question if the stories are true.

What troubles me most is how the book shows Muhammad as a kind and humble man. This does not match with what history tells us about how he gained power. I wonder if Muslims today know the full story of how Muhammad became a leader.

The ideas Jesus taught during his life were quickly changed as Christian thinking grew after his death. Looking at history, we can see Christianity moved further from what Jesus first taught. Today, more people seem to understand this and want change. While some people want to keep old ways of thinking, they may be too few to stop change.

In the years ahead, Christians will learn more about their history. They will want to know what Jesus really meant to teach, separate from ideas added later. This may take many years, but change will come. Christian thinking will go back toward its start. People will remove added teachings one by one, like going back in time. They will continue until only Jesus' original message from God remains.

When this happens in America and Europe, many people will try to follow only what Jesus taught. Churches will still be important to lead this change. As people go back to earlier ways, the many different Christian groups will become more alike. Instead of having many different beliefs, Christians will share more common ideas.

History shows us big changes can happen. The Romans once killed Christians, but later became Christian themselves. America once had slaves, but now has African-American leaders. Christianity will also see big changes as people look for its true beginning.

To understand Jesus better, people will need to see that he often spoke in word pictures rather than direct statements. But how did Christianity change from what Jesus taught?

If we look back far enough, we find only the Jewish religion, which came before Christianity. By the time Rome took control of Jerusalem in 63 BCE, Jewish people believed in one God, followed their holy books, and thought God had given them their religion. But Jewish people were divided into different groups: the Sadducees, Pharisees, Essenes, Zealots, and most people who did not belong to any group.

I think "The Jungle" shows that people are naturally wanting things only for themselves. They care about making their own lives better but do not help others who have less than they do. This book shows this idea in many ways.

The most clear example is how factory owners and managers act. They only want to make their businesses bigger and richer. They do not care who gets hurt when they try to grow their companies. In the book, Upton Sinclair writes about big buildings with smoke coming from tall chimneys, spreading far into the sky. He wants to show how the factory smoke hurts everything around it. The owners do not care about people or animals who might get sick. They ignore the dark smoke from their factories and the animal waste that runs from the many animal pens in Packingtown.

The owners and managers also do not care about the workers who make them rich. They will do anything to save or make more money. Workers might lose their jobs without any warning. During this time, there were few laws to protect workers. This meant owners could make people work long hours in dangerous places. The workers had to accept these bad conditions both at work and where they lived.

The poor workers had no one to help them. While there were some worker groups called unions, these often took money from the workers instead of helping them. The workers were treated so badly that they were like slaves. Most were poor people from other countries who were always close to having no food. They had to do whatever the cruel factory owners wanted, just like slaves had to obey their masters.

Edgar Allan Poe wrote a poem called "Dream-Land" which he thought was one of his best works. In this poem, he uses the word "Thule" two times. This word comes from old stories about a far-away land in the north, past Britain. While the word appeared in very old writings, Poe likely knew it from more recent German writing.

Poe read many German writers. One of these writers was named Goethe, who wrote a famous story called "Faust." Inside "Faust" is a shorter poem about "The King of Thule." This poem tells of a sad king whose wife died after giving him a special cup. The king drinks a lot and cries because he misses his dead wife. Finally, he gives away everything except the cup. He then walks to a high place above the sea, throws the cup into the water, and dies.

The king in Goethe's poem is much like the person in Poe's "Dream-Land." Both stories show dark, lonely places and sad people who have lost loved ones. Poe used the word "Thule" in another story called "The Pit and the Pendulum" around the same time.

When we read both poems together, we can see how they are alike. In "Dream-Land," the writer talks about a dark place where he sees dead friends and a world without bright colors. This is very similar to the king's story in Goethe's poem, where he is alone and sad after his wife's death.

Poe knew about Goethe's writing because Goethe was very famous at that time. Many people were making new versions of his works, and Poe, who read a lot, would have known these stories well.

Let me explain a case about safety in a store in California. A woman named Jennifer Palmer fell in a store and wants the court to make the store pay extra money as punishment. Here's what happened:

On October 13, someone spilled applesauce in D&D Markets. Two workers told the store manager, Paul Martin, about the spill. The first worker told him at 5:00 PM, and another worker told him again at 5:15 PM. Martin did not clean it up because he was eating his dinner. At 5:30 PM, Palmer fell on the spill and hurt her back badly.

The store had problems with safety before. Five other people had fallen in the store that same year. Palmer believes the manager acted very badly by not cleaning the spill when he knew about it.

In California, people can get extra money in court if someone acts very badly toward them. The law says the bad actions must show the person clearly knew they could hurt someone but did not care. The manager knew about other people falling before, and still did not clean up the spill for thirty minutes.

A judge will probably let Palmer ask for extra punishment money. This is because:
1. The manager knew about the spill
2. He was told twice about it
3. He knew other people had fallen before
4. He still chose not to clean it up

The law says this kind of behavior - knowing something is dangerous but not fixing it - can be punished with extra money beyond just paying for the injury.

She always felt she needed something in her life. This feeling started when she was 14 years old and continued until she was 17. She knew she wanted to find someone special, but no boys interested her. Some boys liked her and tried to get her attention, but she felt nothing for them. She often wondered why she was different from other young people her age. After thinking about it for years, she still had no clear answer.

Life at home was usually quiet. Her parents were peaceful people who rarely fought. They only disagreed when their daughter wanted more freedom. While her parents were calm, she was full of life and fun. People liked her because she was both interesting and kind.

But this day was different. As she walked through the house looking for something to do, she heard her mother cry out in the kitchen. She ran to help, asking, "Mom, are you all right?" Her mother was on the floor, clearly hurting. Between deep breaths, her mother said she needed to go to the hospital. The daughter helped lift her mother carefully. She was glad she had learned how to lift heavy things properly. She carried her mother to the car, placed her in the back seat, and drove to the hospital.

The hospital had strong smells, but she did not notice them. She was too worried about her mother. She carried her mother inside and called for help. Medical workers quickly came and moved her mother onto a bed with wheels. They took her mother away for care, leaving the daughter to wait alone.

Later, she learned her mother had fallen from a small ladder while trying to reach a flower container from a high shelf.

This study looked at how eating foods common to countries near the Mediterranean Sea might help prevent heart and blood vessel problems. The eating plan includes lots of plant foods, fish, and healthy oils. It has less meat and animal fat. Small amounts of wine are allowed.

Earlier studies showed that people who followed this eating plan had better health and lived longer. They also found it helped overweight people lose weight better than just eating less fat.

The study watched 74,886 women between ages 38 and 63 for twenty years. All were nurses working in eleven different states. None had heart problems or diabetes when the study began. Every few years, the women filled out forms about what they ate. Almost all the women stayed in the study for the full twenty years.

The researchers checked hospital records and death certificates to confirm when women had heart attacks or strokes. They also looked at other things that affect health, like exercise, smoking, and medicine use.

To make the food information more accurate, they averaged what each woman ate over several years. They also considered other things that could affect the results, like age and exercise.

The study found that women who followed the Mediterranean eating plan most closely had fewer heart problems and strokes. During the twenty years, 2,391 women had heart problems, 1,763 had strokes, and 1,077 died from heart disease or stroke. Women who followed the eating plan best were much less likely to have these health problems compared to those who followed it least.

A woman stands on a street holding a sign. She is the actor Ellen Page, known from movies. Her sign speaks about a bad situation in Burma, a country also called Myanmar.

Burma has been controlled by military leaders since 1962. In 2007, people began to protest in the streets for the first time in many years. Many of these protesters were religious men wearing orange clothes. When the protests grew bigger, the military leaders became angry. They attacked the religious buildings and hurt many people. They also stopped news workers from other countries from showing what was happening. One news picture-taker from Japan was killed just for being there. The government said only 13 people died, but a military leader who left his job said thousands were killed.

This kind of control over people is not new. Throughout time, leaders have tried to stop people from speaking against them. In old Rome, leaders said the gods chose them to rule everyone. In Japan, people once believed their leaders were gods. Even today, some leaders try to control what people think and do.

There are other sad examples from recent times. In China in 1989, students and workers gathered to protest against their government. Many were killed, perhaps thousands. In Rwanda in the 1990s, one group of people tried to kill another group, and many died. In the 1930s and 1940s, Hitler killed millions of Jewish people in many countries.

Duke Ellington was very important to jazz music. He led his band for many years and knew how to write music that made each player sound their best. While he played piano, his greatest skill was writing music. He created pieces that let musicians play freely while also writing parts that needed to be played exactly as written.

He understood how each person in his band played and used this knowledge to make new and exciting music. He knew how to make all the different sounds work together to create something special.

One famous piece called "Creole Love Call" shows how Ellington used the human voice like another instrument in the band, without using words. This slow blues song has six main parts:

Part 1: Voice and wind instruments take turns playing
Part 2: Soft trumpet plays alone
Part 3: High clarinet plays with quiet piano
Part 4: Full band plays together
Part 5: Wind instruments play high notes while others keep time
Part 6: Voice and winds play together again, with the voice making special sounds
Ending: Voice runs up and down while trombone adds final notes

In other songs like "Hot and Bothered," Ellington mixed singing with instrument sounds in new ways. He had a trumpet player named Bubber Miley play back and forth with a singer named Baby Cox. In "It Don't Mean a Thing," he used a trombone player called Tricky Sam to start the song in a special way.

These pieces show how Ellington was very good at mixing different sounds to make interesting music. He knew exactly how to use each person's special talents in his band.

How do living things change over time? Are there limits that guide how they change? In 1917, a scientist named D'Arcy Thompson said that we could not yet describe living things using numbers and math. This is still true today.

Recently, scientists have used math to study how sea animal shells grow and change over time. Our study looks at a type of sea animal called Prunum. We want to understand how these shells grow and change from parent to child, and over many years.

We took X-ray pictures of different Prunum shells to measure their shapes. We put these measurements into a computer program called CerioShell. This helped us create pictures of possible shell shapes. By studying these shapes and doing tests, we can better understand how these animals change over long periods.

A shell is like a tube that turns in a circle many times. These turns are called whorls. The whorls turn around a center line called the columella. Each whorl is separated by a line called a suture. The biggest whorl is usually the last one, called the body whorl. All other whorls make up the spire. The top of the spire is called the apex, and the bottom is called the base. The animal comes out through a hole called the aperture.

You can look at shells from different views: from the top (apical), bottom (basal), front (apertural), and back (abapertural). Usually, people look at shells from the front, with the opening facing them and the top pointing up.

To count whorls, look at the shell from the top. Find where the first line (suture) starts. Draw a line to split the shell in two parts. Count the whorls from this line. You can count parts of whorls in quarters.

As the animal builds its shell, it makes new openings that follow a path through space. We can track this path by measuring the center of each opening and how wide and tall it is.

We can show this path using pictures and math. Once we understand the math, we can change different parts to see how the shell might grow differently.

In Indonesia, the number of babies and young children who die has stayed almost the same for ten years. The country has made progress in some areas, like providing clean water. However, it has not made enough progress in keeping mothers and children healthy. There are many reasons for this, which suggest the whole health system needs to be stronger.

More births now happen with trained health workers present - about 72 out of 100 births. However, many of these workers are traditional birth helpers who cannot help if something goes wrong during birth. This is why many mothers still die from losing too much blood. Also, fewer sick children under five years old are being seen by doctors. We also know that not enough mothers get care after having their babies.

Special operations to help mothers give birth safely (called c-sections) are not happening enough - only 4 out of 100 births. In cities, 7 out of 100 mothers get these operations, but in rural areas, only 2 out of 100 do. This shows that health care is better in cities than in rural areas. Also, rich people get much more health care than poor people. The difference is very large - 27 out of 100. Poor people often cannot pay for health care.

To make things better, Indonesia must decide how to fix these problems. They could start special programs just for mothers and babies, or they could make the whole health system better. Special programs might work faster and be easier to manage. But these programs can cause problems. When a lot of money goes to one health program, other health services get less money and fewer workers. Also, having many different programs doing the same work wastes time and resources. Workers must fill out too many papers to get supplies and money.

Over the past hundred years, popular music has grown to include many different kinds. Today, there are so many kinds of music that it is hard to list them all. Each kind of music, like rap, rock, country, jazz, and folk, has created many smaller groups within itself.

Heavy Metal rock music has become one of the most interesting kinds of popular music in the past forty years. It shows many different feelings, usually dark ones. Soon after Heavy Metal began, people found they could change it in many ways. This led to many new forms of Heavy Metal music, and this continues today.

Now there are so many different kinds of Heavy Metal that it is hard to say exactly what Heavy Metal is. It has taken ideas from many other kinds of music. To understand Heavy Metal music today, we must understand how it started and why it became more than just another kind of music.

Heavy Metal is often about dark things. It uses more of everything - more deep sounds, more loud noise, and more angry words. The people who play Heavy Metal must be very good at playing their instruments. In the middle of the 1970s, many music players used drugs, which led them to make strange music. Heavy Metal was different from other popular music because it showed the darker side of life. Some of these dark ideas came from music written hundreds of years ago.

One of the first Heavy Metal songs might have been "Helter Skelter" by the Beatles. They wrote this song to show they could make music as strong as the Rolling Stones. The song had dark words and showed the effects of drugs. They put this song on their White Album.

Many years before artists began making strange dream-like pictures, Henri Rousseau was already painting his own dreams. His famous work "The Dream" from 1910 shows a woman looking with wonder at the land she sees in her sleep. The painting also shows what Rousseau himself wanted as an artist. He always hoped other artists and art lovers would accept and praise his work, but this was not easy to achieve. "The Dream" shows how Rousseau had to choose between two paths: he could either copy other artists to be accepted, or he could make his own special kind of art.

To understand this painting better, we should know about Rousseau's life. He was born on May 21, 1844, in Laval, France. His father fixed metal objects and sold hardware, and had enough money to live well. Rousseau never went to art school. Instead, he worked for the city collecting money from people at road gates until he was forty years old. People wrongly called him a customs worker. His life was very sad at times - his first wife died, and eight of his babies did not live. Only his daughter Julia lived. To feel better, he started painting.

Unlike other artists of his time who made pretty pictures of poor people, Rousseau painted like a common person because that is what he was. He wanted very much to be accepted by other artists. This wish makes sense because he started painting late in life and had no training. He was making art at the same time as many famous artists. For example, when Rousseau finally started getting noticed, another artist named Matisse was becoming well-known. A writer named Jan Gordon said these two artists were very different: Matisse tried hard not to paint like everyone else, while Rousseau just wanted to paint pictures that would make other artists accept him.

Many wise people have seen a close link between what is good and what is beautiful. I believe there is a deep reason for this connection. The poet John Keats wrote that beauty and truth are the same thing, and this is all we need to know.

We learn most things in life through school or from our own experiences. But we seem to understand what is good and beautiful naturally, without being taught. When we study good behavior or beautiful art, we try to explain why they are special, rather than make rules about them.

When we talk about art or good behavior, we can never fully explain why they move us. For example, people might discuss the famous Mona Lisa painting by looking at its colors or its place in history. But these details do not really tell us why it is great art. Often, when people talk about art they love, they first say, "There is just something about it." I think both art and good behavior have qualities that cannot be fully described in words.

The writer Flannery O'Connor once said that we tell stories because simple statements are not enough. No matter how carefully we describe a book or painting, something special remains unexplained. Good behavior is the same way. There is always something more that we feel but cannot put into words.

I believe art and good behavior are closely connected because we feel them deeply in our hearts, even when we cannot explain them fully. This is especially true with books and stories. Literature is different from other arts because it deals directly with how people should live. When we read, we think about what is right and wrong, just as we do in real life. This is why literature is so important to us.

Today's Germany is one strong nation. It has its own special way of life that can be found from the mountains in Munich to the northern city of Kiel on the sea. This same way of life exists from Cologne on the Rhine River to Dresden on the Elbe River in the east. Germany's special culture comes from many different groups of people who lived there long ago.

The old land of the German people was called Germania. No one knows for sure how it got this name. A writer named Tacitus said the name came from a group called the Tungrians, who were known as Germans before they crossed the Rhine River to fight their neighbors. Julius Caesar was the first to write the word "Germanus" when he wrote about his wars. He learned this word from the people he had already won in battle, to tell them apart from the people he had not yet won. Some think the name means "neighbor" in the old language. Others think it comes from the word for the fighting stick they used, or from words that mean "to shout."

Tacitus wrote in the year 98 that the German people were the first to live in their land. He thought they did not mix with other groups. He asked who would leave warm lands to come to this cold place with dark skies unless it was already their home.

The Romans did not want to live in Germania. They went there to get goods and sometimes to fight, but they usually went back to Rome. The German groups began to appear about two thousand years ago. They lived near the edge of Roman lands. They traded goods they found in their land, and some fought in the Roman army.

In Shakespeare's play Twelfth Night, we learn about hiding who we really are. The story shows that while pretending to be someone else can help for a while, people must eventually return to their true selves. If they do not, they might lose their real identity. However, when someone stops pretending, they might lose friends. So people must choose between staying true to themselves or keeping their relationships with others.

The story looks closely at women pretending to be men. This brings up an important question: why would someone need to hide their true self? In the play, Viola, the main character, does this to stay safe. She says she needs help from a captain to change her clothes and serve a noble count.

Viola is in a new place and feels she must act like a man to protect herself. This works, but it creates problems. She cannot make friends with other women, which leaves her alone. Things get worse when Olivia, another woman in the play, thinks Viola is a man named Cesario and falls in love with her. Also, Viola develops feelings for Orsino, a man who thinks she is a male servant.

For today's readers, the play shows how pretending to be someone else can bring hidden feelings to light. This is true for both Olivia and Orsino. Some might wonder if Olivia loves Cesario because she thinks Cesario is a man, or if she might have deeper, hidden feelings for women. But this is probably not what Shakespeare meant. Instead, he seems to be making fun of people who only care about how others look.

We can see this when Olivia quickly changes her love from Cesario to Sebastian (Viola's twin brother) and starts to think of Viola as family instead of someone to love. She even calls Viola "sister" at the end of the play.

The German control of other lands in Africa was often cruel. This was especially true in South West Africa, where they killed many local Ovaherero and Nama people. However, the way Germans ruled different areas varied greatly. In some places, they helped local people learn to read and write. When the British took control of German East Africa in 1919, they found many educated African people there. Other writers also said good things about German schools in places like Kamerun.

The story was very different in South West Africa, which is now called Namibia. Unlike East Africa, where the government built schools for local people, in South West Africa they left teaching to church groups. These groups got little help from the government. However, the government spent much money on schools for white European children. They built their own schools and gave more money to church schools for white children. This affected South West Africa for many years. While other German-controlled areas had many educated African people, in South West Africa most local people could not read or write. Many things caused this difference, including the way white settlers and government leaders thought about African people.

Many people have written about schools in German-controlled areas. Most early writing was in German, from the time when Germany controlled these places. These writers mostly told about how the schools worked. Later, English writers compared schools in different German-controlled areas. They showed how different these places were. One important writer, Cohen, looked closely at schools in South West Africa and East Africa. He found that the large number of white settlers in South West Africa made its schools very different.

South West Africa had weather that white people could live in more easily, even though much of the land was dry desert. By 1913, almost 15,000 white people lived there. The next highest number was in East Africa, with only 5,336 white people.

The United States and Mexico were not friendly nations for many years, from 1836 to 1893. The worst time in their relationship was during the Mexican-American War from 1846 to 1848. In this war, the United States fought Mexico and won. As a result, the United States took control of Texas and other land in the southwest.

The two countries had many differences that caused problems. They did not share the same religion, culture, or ways of life. This is common when two countries share a border. Mexico and Cuba are the only countries in the Americas that had long-lasting problems with the United States.

Religion was a big reason for the problems between the United States and Mexico. In the 1800s, Americans did not like Catholic countries, just as they later did not like communist countries in the 1900s. This dislike came from old problems between England and Spain, the countries that once controlled the United States and Mexico.

During the 57 years of poor relations, the United States and Mexico had 17 different fights or disagreements. Most of these problems happened because bad people would cross the border to cause trouble. Both countries had to use their armies to stop these attacks.

The problems between the two countries began to get better when Mexico started to depend more on the United States. By the end of the 1800s, the United States stopped trying to take Mexican land and instead became interested in doing business with Mexico.

Fifteen years ago, I became sick with an illness I did not know about. I could no longer work. I had been a nurse then.

I became a nurse because I wanted to feel safe. As a child, I did not feel safe. People told me, "You will always have work because people will always be sick." I really wanted to be a scientist or write news stories, but I chose to be a nurse instead.

Then, at age 46, I was alone and had very little money. I could not work. Today, I still cannot work. After fifteen years of getting help money from the government, I own almost nothing. Each day is hard. I do not feel safe or good about myself. Nothing is sure anymore. But I know one thing: I could not have lived these years without help from my family and friends. When bad things happen, you do not feel strong.

Life will always have big and small problems. You cannot be ready for everything. Some problems are too big to face alone.

I agree that Americans should not depend only on the government. But I would rather see Americans help each other instead of trying to live alone.

Some people talk about how Americans should be strong alone. But what really helped our early people was working together and sharing. The people who went west in wagons did not make it alone.

Yes, be ready for problems. I am ready. I have things for when bad times come: medical supplies, clean water items, and food that stays good for a long time. If you can grow food or save food, that is good. If you can have a wood stove, that is also good.

But also, know the people who live near you.

Around 2,500 years ago, a prince was born who would later be known as Buddha. During his life, he left his wealthy life behind and found deep wisdom. His teachings created Buddhism, and the oldest form is called Theravada Buddhism.

The religion has changed much since Buddha's time. In Sri Lanka, where many follow Theravada Buddhism, people take part in a yearly water ceremony. Both religious teachers and regular people join this event. While Buddha never spoke about such celebrations, they have become important to the people.

These changes are not just about celebrations. They touch the deep ideas of what it means to find peace and freedom from suffering. The Buddhist community, both teachers and followers, has needed to change some of their basic beliefs over time. These changes happened because of different reasons, some from inside the Buddhist community and some from outside. Some changes came from people who wanted to hurt Buddhism, while others happened naturally.

The main teachings of Buddhism are quite clear. Buddhists follow three important things: Buddha himself, his teachings (called Dhamma), and the community of Buddhist teachers (called Sangha). The teachings are written in three main groups of books. These books talk about how to live, how to behave, and how the world works.

The books teach that nothing stays the same forever, that life includes suffering, and that people do not have a permanent soul. Understanding these ideas helps people break free from being born again and again. When someone gains this understanding, they can end bad feelings like wanting too much, being angry, and being confused.

Buddhist teachers must follow many rules. Regular followers have five main rules: do not kill, do not lie, do not steal, do not act badly in love matters, and do not drink things that confuse the mind. The most important teaching is that life brings suffering, that wanting things causes suffering, but that we can find a way to end this suffering.
